============================================================
Reference projects (consulted, no code copied)
============================================================

The following projects were studied to understand the underlying
protocols and behaviors XV implements. No source code from these
projects has been copied or adapted into XV; XV's implementations
were written independently. Specific design decisions informed by
each reference are noted inline in the XV source.

  - Mumla (https://gitlab.com/quite/mumla) — Mumble timing and
    voice-packet conventions. Referenced for `frameSamples = 480`
    (10ms @ 48kHz). License: GPL-3.0.

  - Humla (https://github.com/quite/humla) — Mumble protocol
    integration patterns, in particular the UDP_TUNNEL raw-payload
    behavior. License: GPL-3.0. No code copied; only behavior referenced.

  - jeffypooo/aina-android
    (https://github.com/jeffypooo/aina-android) — AINA APTT V1 SPP
    retry conventions. License: MIT. Referenced for the 3-attempt
    connect-burst pattern.

============================================================
Vendor-supplied documentation
============================================================

  - AINA APTT Bluetooth communication protocol documentation v18
    and UI spec v10 (https://ainaptt.com/developers/) — used to
    implement V1 ASCII protocol parsing (AinaAsciiParser) and V2
    BLE GATT button-mask decoding (ButtonMaskDecoder, AinaBleReader).
    No vendor code; reverse-implemented from published spec.

  - Mumble wire protocol specification
    (https://www.mumble.info/documentation/development/protocol/)
    — voice-packet framing, varint encoding (MumbleVoicePacket).
